Can you have too much #Bitcoin? 

The answer is an unequivocal "Yes!" You CAN have too much #btc and here are the signs that you may have too much at the current moment.

You have too much #BTC when:

1) Your quality of life has deteriorated to the point where the USD price has you super stressed at all times, you can't sleep and you are generally miserable all the time;

2) A downward movement of 20% to 30% makes you feel as though your whole life is over and you start entertaining thoughts that #btc is a farce;

3) The downward USD prices cause you to quickly sell, in order to wait for lower prices; 

4) You start following crypto bros and YouTube influencers each day in search of instructions and  guidance on what to do with your #btc; 

5) You have zero cash to live your ordinary life. Note: Many Bitcoiners disagree with me on this one, but I'll hold my ground on this. #BTC is the world's greatest saving technology. It is not yet the world's greatest spending technology. We still need dirty cash for our daily lives. Having the appropriate amount of cash on hand to live your life normally without causing your family to suffer just because your profile picture suddenly has laser eyes is more than ok, it's intelligence. My 2 sats.

At the end of the day, if what we believe to be true about #Bitcoin and its potential has merit, having a truck load is simply not necessary. What is more necessary is that you hold on to what you have without selling it. That to me is more important than the quantity, especially at the start of your journey. 

Lastly, as your understanding about and conviction in #Bitcoin grows, you'll only up your comfort level and go for more and more and more. That is what happened to me. I hope this helps. #stackharder

